Title : Francis Brooks Chadwick
Text : {{Short description|American-French painter}}
[[File:EChadwick-Husband.jpg|thumb|200px|Francis Brooks Chadwick: portrait by his wife]]
'''Francis Brooks Chadwick''' (January 1, 1850&ndash;1942/43), was an American painter active in France.

[[File:Francis Brooks Chadwick.jpg|thumb|left|Francis Brooks Chadwick, [[John Singer Sargent]], 1880]]

He was born in Boston and studied at Harvard, and to pursue his interest in art he attended the [[Académie Julian]] in Paris. He was friends with the painter John Singer Sargent and travelled with him to Haarlem in 1880. The following year he married the Swedish painter [[Emma Chadwick|Emma Löwstädt-Chadwick]] and they settled in [[Grez-sur-Loing]], where he remained the rest of his life, though the couple travelled to other summer art colonies on vacation.<ref>[http://cornwallartists.org/cornwall-artists/francis-brooks-chadwick Francis Brooks Chadwick] on website for artists active in Cornwall</ref>

He is known for scenes of Grez.<ref>[http://www.berry-hill.com/artists/francis-brooks-chadwick/ Francis Brooks Chadwick] on Berry-hill gallery website</ref>

